        "comment": {
            "name": "comment",
            "type": "com.atlassian.jira.issue.fields.CommentSystemField",
            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/40420",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=bittarman",
                        "name": "bittarman",
                        "displayName": "Ryan Mauger",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "My opinion is that this is better implemented with routes as it currently stands.\r\n\r\nThe reasoning for this is when you have the url foo\/bar\/baz, would that be (module => foo, controller => bar, action => baz) or (controller => foo, action => bar, param => baz) ?\r\n\r\nThis will only lead to extra confusion, and would lead to an inconsistent workflow for developers.\r\n\r\nKeeping this to its current requirement to add an explicit route removes this ambiguity, and provides a consistent workflow. ",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=bittarman",
                        "name": "bittarman",
                        "displayName": "Ryan Mauger",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-05-10T10:25:34.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-05-10T10:25:34.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/40421",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=loconut",
                        "name": "loconut",
                        "displayName": "The Lone Coder",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "It was pointed out that in the case where you have ambiguous controller and module naming such as:\r\n<Bittarman> \/foo\/bar\/baz is that module => foo, controller => bar, action => baz, or controller => foo, action => bar, param => baz\r\n\r\nPersonally, it seems like a bad idea to have controllers and modules named the same in the first place, and perhaps the default parameter should only be available on the default module to help reduce conflicts. Since the goal is shortening URLs here, once you're already listing \/module\/controller\/action, your URLs are arguably too long to bother shortening.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=loconut",
                        "name": "loconut",
                        "displayName": "The Lone Coder",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-05-10T10:26:59.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-05-10T10:26:59.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/40422",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=loconut",
                        "name": "loconut",
                        "displayName": "The Lone Coder",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Either way, it's just an idea.",
